magpie.data.utilities.generators

Class BaseEntryGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • magpie.data.utilities.generators.BaseEntryGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<BaseEntry>, Options
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AlloyingCompositionEntryGenerator, CompositionRangeEntryGenerator, GridBaseEntryGenerator, PhaseDiagramCompositionEntryGenerator, PrototypeEntryGenerator

    public abstract class BaseEntryGenerator
extends java.lang.Object
implements Options, java.lang.Iterable<BaseEntry>
    Base for classes that generate new entries.

    How to use:

    1. Define options for entry generation as desired
    2. Call generateEntries() to create a list of new entries
    3. Or, add them automatically to a dataset using generateEntries()

    How to implement:

    1. Create a class name that implies what kind of BaseEntry is generated
    2. Define class variables that hold any user options
    3. Create operations that allow the user to set those options
    4. Implement the Options interface
    5. Implement the generateEntries() command, which should take whatever settings the user defined into account
